# Stack Layout Shifts

This is a critical rule for this project.

## Core rule

- Never move just one section in isolation.
- When a section is moved down the page, every section below it must also move down to maintain the correct order.
- Never leave sections overlapping or out of sequence after a move.
- Treat the page layout like a stack: if one block shifts, everything beneath it shifts too.

## Applies everywhere

- This applies regardless of CSS layout method:
  - absolute positioning
  - flexbox
  - grid
  - transforms
  - margins
  - top/left offsets
  - any other layout mechanism

## Required check

- If asked to "move a section down", always inspect what is below it.
- Move all lower sections by the same effective delta unless Sam explicitly asks for a different relationship.
- Preserve ordering, spacing rhythm, and non-overlap after the shift.

## For this portfolio

- Timeline rows, hero blocks, mobile case-study sections, screenshots, and paired copy blocks must keep their sequence intact after any move.
- Do not create a local fix that pushes one block into the next block's space.
